---
title: Pizza Burgers with Balsamic Arugula Salad
description: Picking between pizza and burgers for dinner is a choice no one should have to make. Luckily, our chefs are masters of compromise. They’ve come up with a recipe that features the best of both: it starts with a classic beef patty, gives it a toasted ciabatta bun, and then brings in hearty tomato sauce and an Italian cheese blend. The best part? It’s ready in less time than it’d take to order delivery (or take a spin ’round the drive-thru).
image: https://img.hellofresh.com/f_auto,fl_lossy,h_640,q_auto,w_1200/hellofresh_s3/image/pizza-burgers-38eccacf.jpg
pdf: https://www.hellofresh.com/recipecards/card/pizza-burgers-5877f484.pdf
course: main course
source: https://www.hellofresh.com/recipes/pizza-burgers-59fb796e05346808b55bae52
servings: 2
author: Olwen Phillips
cuisine: North America
nutrition:
  calories: 770 kcal
  fat: 41 g
  saturated fat: 15 g
  carbohydrates: 54 g
  sugar: 10 g
  protein: 44 g
  fiber: 6 g
  sodium: 930 mg
time required: 20 minutes
---

Wash and dry all produce. Preheat #toaster oven{} or #oven{} to 400 degrees. Halve, peel, and finely dice @red onion{1}. Split @ciabatta bread{2} in half, creating bun tops and bottoms. Place @whole peeled tomatoes{14%ounce} in a #medium bowl{} and crush with hands until you have no pieces larger than ½ inch.

Heat a large drizzle of @vegetable oil{1%tablespoon} in a #large pan{} over medium-high heat. Add onion and season with @salt{}, @pepper{}, and half the @Italian seasoning{1/2%tablespoon}. Cook, tossing, until softened, ~{2-3%minutes}. Add tomatoes and stir to combine. Bring to a boil, then lower heat and reduce to a gentle simmer. Keep simmering until rest of meal is ready.

Heat a drizzle of @vegetable oil{} in another large pan. Combine @ground beef{10%ounce} and remaining @Italian seasoning{1/2%tablespoon} in another medium bowl, then shape into two patties slightly wider than ciabattas. Season with salt and pepper. Add to pan and cook to desired doneness, ~{2-4%minutes} per side; ~{1%minute} before burgers are done, sprinkle @Italian cheese blend{1/2%cup} on top, cover pan, and let melt.

Place ciabatta halves in toaster oven or oven and toast until golden brown, ~{3-5%minutes}.

> TIP: Use a #baking sheet{} if toasting in the oven.

Toss @arugula{2%ounce} in a #large bowl{} with a large drizzle of @olive oil{2%teaspoon} and @balsamic vinegar{1%tablespoon} (we sent more). Season with salt and pepper.

> TIP: Use the remaining vinegar if you want a more tangy salad.

Divide ciabatta bottoms between plates, then spread with tomato sauce. Top each with a burger and a little more tomato sauce, then place remaining ciabatta halves on top.

> TIP: You'll have some sauce left over—save it for another use, such as mixing into pasta.